%S A397751 3,0,2,3,2,5,3,7,8,3,15,11,3,26,14,3,40,17,3,57,20,3,77,23,3,100,26,3,
%T A397751 126,29,3,155,32,3,187,35,3,222,38,3,260,41,3,301,44,3,345,47,3,392,
%U A397751 50,3,442,53,3,495,56,3,551,59,3,610,62,3,672,65,3,737,68,3,805
%N A397751 Number of minimum independent dominating sets in the n-cycle graph.
%C A397751 The n-cycle graph is defined for n >= 3. The sequence has been extended to n = 0 using the formula.
%H A397751 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A397751/b397751.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%H A397751 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CycleGraph.html">Cycle Graph</a>.
%H A397751 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/IndependentDominatingSet.html">Independent Dominating Set</a>.
%H A397751 <a href="/index/Rec#order_09">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (0,0,3,0,0,-3,0,0,1).
%F A397751 a(3*n) = 3; a(3*n+1) = n*(3*n + 1)/2 = A005449(n); a(3*n+2) = 3*n + 2.
%F A397751 a(n) = 3*a(n-3) - 3*a(n-6) + a(n-9).
%F A397751 G.f.: (3 + 2*x^2 - 6*x^3 + 2*x^4 - x^5 + 3*x^6 + x^7 - x^8)/((1 - x)^3*(1 + x + x^2)^3).
%e A397751 The a(4) = 2 independent dominating sets are:
%e A397751      x---o     o---x
%e A397751      |   |     |   |
%e A397751      o---x     x---o
%e A397751 The a(6) = 3 independent dominating sets are:
%e A397751      x---o---o    o---x---o     o---o---x
%e A397751      |       |    |       |     |       |
%e A397751      o---o---x    o---x---o     x---o---o
%o A397751 (PARI) Vec((3 + 2*x^2 - 6*x^3 + 2*x^4 - x^5 + 3*x^6 + x^7 - x^8)/((1 - x)^3*(1 + x + x^2)^3) + O(x^81))
%Y A397751 Cf. A005449, A302653, A347538, A397750 (for path graph).
%K A397751 nonn,easy,new
%O A397751 0,1
%A A397751 _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 13 2026
